Sentencas: The development of triple-conductivity (H+/O2-/e(-)) durable cathode with effective oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) activity is significant to boost the application of proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell (H-SOFC) at intermediate-to-low-temperature.
Titulo: Pr0.7Ba0.3Co0.8-xFe0.2NixO3-δ perovskite: High activity and durable cathode for intermediate-to-low-temperature proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Herein, we developed the Pr0.7Ba0.3Co0.8-xFe0.2NixO3-delta (x = 0, 0.1, 0.2, 0.3) cathode material with triple-conductivity.
Titulo: Pr0.7Ba0.3Co0.8-xFe0.2NixO3-δ perovskite: High activity and durable cathode for intermediate-to-low-temperature proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Based on the distribution of relaxation time results, it is found that nickel doping enhanced the surface exchange kinetics and boosted bulk charge transfer.
Titulo: Pr0.7Ba0.3Co0.8-xFe0.2NixO3-δ perovskite: High activity and durable cathode for intermediate-to-low-temperature proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: As a result, Pr0.7Ba0.3Co0.6Fe0.2Ni0.2O3-delta (PBCFN2) shows better ORR activity with lower polarization resistance (0.043 Omega cm(2)) and higher power output (1.61 W cm(-2)) for H-SOFC at 700 degrees C. Meanwhile, PBCFN2 also shows suitable durability at 600 degrees C (0.919 A cm(-2) for similar to 105 h).
Titulo: Pr0.7Ba0.3Co0.8-xFe0.2NixO3-δ perovskite: High activity and durable cathode for intermediate-to-low-temperature proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In general, this research may provide a beneficial instruction for further research and optimization for triple-conducting cathodes in intermediate-to-low-temperature H-SOFC.
Titulo: Pr0.7Ba0.3Co0.8-xFe0.2NixO3-δ perovskite: High activity and durable cathode for intermediate-to-low-temperature proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells
